Indonesia: dengue fever outbreak in Medan, North Sumatra
--------------------------------------------------------
MEDAN: At least 145 cases of dengue fever and 3 deaths have been reported
in the North Sumatra capital Medan, health officials said on Wed 6 Aug
2003. Medan health office head Herman Sadeck said the outbreak was an
annual occurrence during the months of July and August, and had always
claimed lives. The varied climate -- sometimes wet and sometimes dry -- had
contributed to the spread of the mosquitoborne disease, he said. The office
recorded 212 cases of dengue fever and 3 deaths last year and 344 cases and
2 deaths in 2001.
